From a6bcba15f793299b08a286bd0e0abf2a538a5636 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 16:23:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#25a-hang (A0): root-cause the ring split-brain + record
 boot regression of the naive fix

Reproduced the brew reinstall hang as a ring<->UDS reply-channel SPLIT-BRAIN in the
perf#18 guest ring: gr_wait_reply()'s slow path is bounded (guard<100000); a make -jN
SIGCHLD storm makes every FUTEX_WAIT return EINTR, exhausting the guard so the guest
abandons the ring and UDS-falls-back, while the server (keyed on _ringReplyPending)
publishes the reply onto the s2c ring nobody reads -> permanent deadlock, server idle,
leaf sh in __unix_dgram_recvmsg. A/B: RING_ON 3/3 hang, RING_OFF (FAST_OPS=0) 2/2 clean.

Tried the surgical option-1 fix (make the ring wait unbounded): it REGRESSED BOOT
(launchd wedges, no shellspawn.sock) -> the UDS fallback is LOAD-BEARING; a ring op's
reply can legitimately arrive over UDS (signal saved-reply / S2C deferred-reply paths
bypass _publishReplyToRingLocked). Reverted byte-identical to baseline 6bd251c3, doctor
GREEN, brew ring-OFF reconfirmed clean.

A0 fix must be SYMMETRIC (guest+server co-design), not fallback removal. Details +
corrected fix shape in tests/PERF25A-BREW-REINSTALL-CENSUS.md (UPDATE 2 + UPDATE 3).
No prod change; recon+revert only.

