Subject: [PATCH] perf#25a-hang (A0): per-fd capture proves it is a SEQPACKET
 aux-channel drain bug, not the ring

/proc/<tid>/syscall + ss -x on a reproduced hang: wedged guest = launchd. Its 3 threads
are each correctly parked in recvmsg on their DGRAM RPC sockets in the perf#21b fd-band
(8189/8190/8191). But TWO SEQPACKET (u_seq) sockets launchd owns at LOW fds 14/39 each
hold 12 bytes UNREAD with NO thread draining them; server peers (fd 16/91) show Send-Q=768
stuck (SEQPACKET backpressure). So the stranded messages are on a connected SEQPACKET
auxiliary channel (fork-checkin / S2C / kqchan, dar-gwn.6.x family), NOT the DGRAM RPC ring
reply path -- which is why both prior ring-targeted fixes failed. Not perf#21b relocation
either (band fds behave; the stranded ones are the low un-relocated SEQPACKET sockets).

NEXT (approved, 1 build cycle): server per-connection instrumentation to name which 12-byte
SEQPACKET aux message strands and which thread should drain it. Detail: PERF25A UPDATE 5,
evidence a0_fd_snapshot.HANG.txt. Prod byte-identical, doctor GREEN.

