The AUXLOG capture named the stranded op (kqchan EVFILT_PROC notification, id=269
launchd->pid473) and the kqchan lost-wakeup fix (c7ea6d9) delivers notifications
reliably (re-arm fires; server PUSHes notif #573 after the last ack). But brew
STILL hangs 1/1: the guest never reads the delivered notification (no proc_read
#574), because launchd never returns to kevent()/epoll_wait — a launchd thread is
wedged in a DGRAM RPC recvmsg (fds 8189-8191) whose reply never arrives, and its
kevent loop (the only drainer of the kqchan) is starved behind that stuck RPC.

So the kqchan backlog is a downstream symptom. Root cause redirected to the
guest-side lost-RPC-reply-under-load family (dar-gwn), now doubly narrowed: NOT the
perf#18 ring (ring-OFF clean) and NOT the kqchan notification gate (this fix is
clean and brew still hangs). Evidence: tmp/a0_auxlog_HANG_afterfix.txt +
a0_auxlog_snapshot.HANG_afterfix.txt. Fix kept on branch (real correctness
improvement) but NOT the cure; prod restored byte-identical to baseline 835946f9.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
