in recvmsg on its DGRAM RPC band fd (8188-8191) with Recv-Q=0 — genuinely waiting
for a reply that was never sent. The kqchan SEQPACKET pile-up (launchd holds 6-7
channels at Recv-Q=12, server peers at Send-Q=768) is confirmed SECONDARY: launchd
can't run its kevent loop to drain them because all its threads are stuck in that
DGRAM RPC.

Root class (evidence-locked): lost/never-sent DGRAM RPC reply (dar-gwn family) —
NOT the ring (counters frozen; ring-OFF historically clean) and NOT the kqchan
notification gate (fixed in c7ea6d9; still hangs). Candidate drop sites: server
never received the call, or the push_reply/InterruptExit saved-reply re-delivery
(call.cpp:176-252/938-958) stranded it, or an S2C/signal reordering + guest
PUSH_UNKNOWN_REPLIES retry (generate-rpc-wrappers.py:1573) pushed the reply back and
it was never re-sent. NEXT: env-gated server per-guest-tid RPC trace (call recv +
reply send, number+tid+target) to name the exact stuck call and drop site.

