cvstorm.c (8 consumers on one condvar + pthread_kill storm) reproduces the fault in
SECONDS on baseline 835946f9 — panics the server instead of only livelocking. Mechanism:
dtape_thread_sigexc_enter pre-clears TH_WAIT, so clear_wait_internal takes KERN_NOT_WAITING
and skips thread_go/thread_unblock, leaving the unblock half-done; the EINTR-retry re-enters
assert_wait with thread->waitq!=NULL -> panic. Hypothesis to be TESTED on the repro (not
assumed). Fast deterministic target replaces the slow noisy brew gate.

