deterministic repro on baseline panicked the server: 'thread already waiting' at
waitq.c:2835 — a thread re-entering assert_wait with thread->waitq!=NULL. Cause:
dtape_thread_sigexc_enter pre-cleared TH_WAIT, so clear_wait_internal took the
KERN_NOT_WAITING branch and skipped thread_go()->thread_unblock(), leaving the
thread half-pulled from its waitq. Fix: clear only TH_UNINT, let clear_wait_internal
own the transition (matches XNU signal-interrupted-wait teardown).

