Instrumented cvstorm on the bd7cdb9 binary drove a new panic 'Bad tailq elm prev->next
!= elm' at locks.c:151 (dtape_mutex_unlock TAILQ_REMOVE). Mechanism: a microthread
suspended in dtape_mutex_lock (mutex_link queued, thread_suspend) is resumed by the
signal-abort path (sigexc->clear_wait->thread_go->thread_resume) INSIDE the retry loop;
if the mutex is still held it TAILQ_INSERT_TAILs the same mutex_link again -> double-link
-> corruption -> in release, unlock wakes a garbage link = lost wakeup = 42:1 livelock.
Reply-stash accounting is healthy (not the driver). Candidate fix: remove own mutex_link
on resume before re-insert. To be tested on the repro.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
