atop the TH_WAIT fix bd7cdb9) produced 7 DOUBLE-INSERT hits, all in dtape_mutex_lock,
each on a mutex_link already queued — while RESULT=HANG. CONFIRMS UPDATE 16: a
signal-aborted wait leaves thread->mutex_link linked (the SAME link backs both the
condvar and mutex queues), and the next dtape_mutex_lock TAILQ_INSERT_TAILs it again ->
corruption -> lost wakeup -> livelock. Mechanism now proven, not assumed. Fix next.

