dtape_thread_create malloc's the thread and memsets only xnu_thread/kwe/default_state,
leaving mutex_link (the shared mutex/condvar wait-queue link + its _dbg_queued flag)
as garbage. The double-insert guard added in 5766b1d reads _dbg_queued on the first
dtape_mutex_lock; nonzero garbage -> a bogus TAILQ_REMOVE on an unqueued link ->
queue corruption at early init -> 'Cannot open mnt namespace file' boot wedge (both the
full fix and the locks.c-only subset wedged identically for THIS reason, not the fix
logic). Zero mutex_link explicitly. Boot re-verification of the full fix in flight.

