   st=0x4 = TH_RUN. All 51,508 sigexc aborts in a run hit an already-RUNNING
   thread; clear_wait_internal correctly returns KERN_NOT_WAITING. A PULL trace
   in waitq_pull_thread_locked showed FAIL=0/OK=60 — the pull never fails. The
   sigexc path is doing nothing wrong; a psynch-blocked consumer is suspended
   and cannot send interrupt_enter, so it never even appears in the sigexc trace.

