DIAGNOSTIC traces (kern_synch.c psynch cvwait/cvsignal/mutexwait/mutexdrop +
ksyn_signal wakeup return; thread.c thread_unblock; thread.cpp Thread::resume +
doWork early-returns) driven on the signal-free repro cvstorm2 -DNCONS=1
-DNO_STORM. Layer-by-layer elimination:

- psynch protocol clean: cvsignal always woke=1; ksyn_signal psynch_wait_wakeup
  always SUCCESS(0), never NOT_WAITING(48).
- mutex is firstfit; _psynch_mutexdrop_internal firstfit branch: ksyn_mtxsignal
  always SUCCESS; DROP-intrpost / DROP-MISS / find_seq never involved.
- microthread resume permit clean: RESUME DROPPED=0; UNBLOCK fires for workers.
- THE BUG: at the freeze, exactly one anomaly across the run:
    A0 DOWORK nstid=30 EARLY-RETURN already-running permit=0
  Thread::doWork() popped a scheduled microthread but hit `if (_running) return;`
  (thread.cpp ~488) and returned WITHOUT running it and WITHOUT rescheduling,
  with the resume permit already consumed -> wake silently dropped -> deadlock.

RACE: _running is cleared only at the doneWorking tail (~629); a waker on a
temporary WorkQueue thread (push() spawns up to hardware_concurrency workers,
workers.hpp:186, even under DSERVER_SINGLE_THREADED) scheduleThread's the
microthread while it's still mid-transition _running. The reverse race
(wake-before-suspend) is covered by _resumePermit; scheduled-while-_running is
NOT. Fix: doWork()'s _running branch must leave a pending-reschedule marker so
doneWorking reschedules once _running clears (invariant: one more doWork after
_running clears). Traces are diagnostic-only; prod byte-identical baseline
835946f9. Repro tmp/cvstorm2.c, harness tmp/a0_cvtrace.sh.

