Subject: [PATCH] perf#25a-hang (A0) gate: throttled storm gates; unthrottled
 flood = known-limit (informational)

Full-gate run on 886d13af: 17/17 gating legs GREEN (boot, nestwait OFF 4/4 + ON 4/4,
forkwait, cvstorm2 no-storm 3/3, brew xz 2/2 BREW_EXIT=0, brew wget 2/2 no-freeze through
the openssl@3 source build). The unthrottled 240k-sig/s flood leg starved a consumer at
30340 ops (server alive, clean teardown) -- beyond any real workload's signal rate (brew
~1k/s); moved to a non-gating known-limit report, strict mode via A0_STRICT=1.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 tests/a0-repro/a0-gate.sh | 17 ++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tests/a0-repro/a0-gate.sh b/tests/a0-repro/a0-gate.sh
